Date: Wed, 18 Mar 1998 18:35:33 -0700
From: Donoghue, Ann <donogha@HESKA.com>

Yikes! I made an error in the post on Balclutha horse syndrome. Horses
are not thought to be susceptible to foot and mouth disease. That
should not have been included in the list of differential diagnoses.
Primarily cloven-hoofed animals are susceptible and few lab
animals [sucking mice and guinea pigs - Mod.PC.
